
Overview of noun asceticism

The noun asceticism has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                   
1. asceticism -- (the doctrine that through renunciation of worldly pleasures it is possible to achieve a high spiritual or intellectual state)
2. austerity, asceticism, nonindulgence -- (the trait of great self-denial (especially refraining from worldly pleasures))
3. asceticism, ascesis -- (rigorous self-denial and active self-restraint)
